1.en: As she answers some of the questions the plant manager is likely to pose, Carol will likely need to set some emergent identity goals.
1.cn: 她回答了工厂经理很可能会提出的一些问题，因为卡罗尔可能需要设置一些偶发身份目标。

2.en: It looks like the set of a Hollywood action movie but these images were taken by a team of expert cave divers in the depths of Russia.
2.cn: 这组照片就像来自好莱坞的场景，但实际上是由一个专业洞穴探险潜水队伍在俄罗斯的深海中拍摄的。

3.en: The last opinion survey shows that, the Conservative Party will win the election, but it is not enough to set up a majority government.
3.cn: 据大选前最后一次民调结果显示，保守党将获得本次选举的胜利，但仍不足以组成多数派政府。

0.en: Around the city of Zhaoqing, eight stations have been set up for the bikers to shake out there soaking ponchos and stop for food.
0.cn: 在肇庆市附近，路上有为骑行者设置的8个站点，能让他们脱下浸透了的雨披，停下来吃些东西。

1.en: A lot of toes were stepped on in order to set this up for today. And frankly, I really don't know what you gentlemen plan to gain by it.
1.cn: 为了设置好今天的这套演示设备，可是折腾了不少人，坦白说，我真不明白你们两位想达到什么目的。

2.cn: 实验室准备就绪了，老大。

3.en: Then one day, I saw you set down.

4.en: They had set a bulldozer on fire.

5.en: Yep. Thank Wolowitz. He set it up.
5.cn: 谢沃罗威茨吧。是他安排的。

6.en: I'll set up a meeting. Just you, me and him.
6.cn: 我会安排次会面，只有你我他三人。

7.en: Hi. I'm gonna need a new set of these forms.

8.en: Maybe we don't need the set-navi. Let's go this way.
8.cn: 也许，我们不需要导航。我们走这边吧。

9.en: So you want to set the record straight. Indeed, Dave.
9.cn: 所以你想建立一个记录。是的，戴夫。

10.en: Your reaction decision time will be set at 35 seconds.
10.cn: 你的反应时间会被设定成35秒。

11.en: You must set aside your petty grievances with the dwarves.
11.cn: 你们对矮人的小牢骚可以放在一边了。

12.en: Think back, Leonard. The littlest things can set women off.
12.cn: 你好好想想，莱纳德，再小的事情都能让女人爆发。

14.en: That could be easily arranged. Ready, set, go? Do it. All right then. Ready. Set. Go.
14.cn: 那真是小菜一碟，各就各位，准备，开始？来吧。那好吧，预备，开始。

15.en: All right, I won't set one aside for you. But I must have it. Okay, I'll set one aside for you.
15.cn: 好吧，那我不给你留了。但我必须要拥有它行。那我给你留着。

16.en: A date? She's got a date? With who? I set her up with this actor on my show. You set her up? No.
16.cn: 她有约会？对方是谁？我撮合她跟一个男演员。你撮合她？不。

17.en: OK. We're all set. What do you mean we're all set? Well, I know that guy. He's gonna take care of it.
17.cn: 好了，我都安排好了。什么意思？安排好什么了？我认识那个人，他会处理好的。

18.en: I will never get sick of you. I am set for life!
18.cn: 我永远都不会烦你。那我此生无忧了！

19.en: I was the one freaking set of footprints in the sand!
19.cn: 我是那被人过了河就拆的桥！
